      • invokeAndWait

        public static void invokeAndWait(Callable<?> task,
                 int timeoutInSeconds)
                          throws Exception
        Runs the given Callable in the JavaFX thread, waiting for it to complete before returning. Also attempts to wait for any other JavaFX events that may have been queued in the Callable to complete. If any Exception is thrown during execution of the Callable, that exception will be re-thrown from invokeAndWait.
